One of my favorite things about making art is the people I meet and the places I get to visit. 
Last week end was a perfect example of this exact point. I traveled to Austin Texas to hand deliver my latest commission to a new collector ( @jeffatx ). I got to meet him and hang out for a few days. I also want to thank my art dealer ( @lanajoliecarlson )for organizing a great reveal event.

This painting based on The Girl with a Pearl Earring is a second and more refined version of a painting I did years ago. I changed the line weight to something more delicate and painted a more organic background. I am happy with this new version as it opened a new path for me to explore. Don't forget to revisit your work and push it forward.

social_posts.post_text:
FLOW

30 x 30 inches.

Acrylic and oil paint on Canvas.
Available for purchase.

I am discovering a new and slower process using oil paint. I love the fact that I have to let the paint dry and I have to live with the art for a while before adding a new layer. This feels like a new chapter in my art story.
